item.description:
In this tutorial, I&rsquo;m going to show you how to use a custom domain for serverless functions exposed as APIs on IBM Cloud. APIs endpoints use a random sub-domain on IBM Cloud by default. Importing your own domains means endpoints can be accessible through custom URLs.
Registering a custom domain with IBM Cloud needs you to complete the following steps&hellip;
 Generate SSL/TLS certificates for your domain Register domain certificates with IBM Certificate Manager Bind a custom domain to Cloud Functions APIs using the IBM Cloud APIs console.
